Merge branch 'nx_fix' into hardening_checks
fix shfmt issues ... again
fix shfmt issues and fix SafeStack process test
fix shellcheck issues and trailing whitespace
Make scripts and binaries executable

Adds a test suite for file and process hardening checks.
To generate the test binaries from scratch call build_binaries.sh.
test.c is used for all binaries and is a simple program that can be built with all supported hardening features. It also includes some of the past edge cases that caused issues in the hardening detection.

Allows process names to include numbers.
Removes unused isString function.
The process name handling was too restrictive and would not allow numbers to be used.

Removes redundant exit at the end of upgrade function.
exit gets called right after the upgrade() call.
Fixes shellcheck SC2317 message.

commit.message:
Fix stack protection check and full relro check.
The " UND " check is sufficient to detect stack protection. Checking the symbol address vaule is not stable between 64 bit and 32 bit binaries and was removed.
Full relro is active if BIND_NOW flag is set or got.plt is not present. There are examples where got.plt is present but will be set to read only so full relro is active.
Merge branch 'nx_fix' of https://github.com/petervas/checksec.sh into nx_fix

Fix NX detection to handle flexible readelf field sizes.
The readelf output format for a binary depends on the architecture the binary was built for.
NX is enabled if the string between the first '0x' and 'RW ' exists and contains the characters ' ', '0' and 'x' only.

commit.message:
Removed s_readelf.
Using the non wide output from readelf for the NX detection is not working when eu-readelf is used. eu-readelf output is always wide.
Changed the NX check accordingly and simplified it.
